Prerequisites for Windows:
Check System Requirements:

Ensure your Windows version is Windows 10 64-bit: Pro, Enterprise, or Education (Build 15063 or later).
Make sure your system supports hardware virtualization and that itâ€™s enabled in the BIOS settings.
Ensure the Windows Subsystem for Linux 2 (WSL 2) feature is enabled.

Download Docker Desktop:

Go to the Docker Desktop for Windows download page.
Click on "Download for Windows".
Install Docker Desktop:

Double-click the downloaded Docker Desktop Installer.exe to run the installer.
Follow the installation wizard steps.
When prompted, authorize the installer and agree to the terms.
Choose "Install required Windows components for WSL 2" if not already installed.
The installer will configure WSL 2 during installation.

Complete the Installation:

Once the installation is complete, Docker Desktop will start automatically.
You might need to sign in with your Docker ID (create one if you don't have it).

Verify Installation by opening a Command Prompt or PowerShell window.
Run docker --version to verify Docker is installed and running.
Run docker run hello-world to verify Docker can pull and run images.

**Example provided at this link**
https://github.com/stephon99/HomeLab/issues/1#issue-2373812769



Follow this link to be brought to the documentation provided by Docker regarding installing Docker Desktop:
https://docs.docker.com/desktop/install/windows-install/
